VdhqokxJng7jBgd2-u6-6lpdzsCuYEXAa-RS_tombhVJDP7SQC\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing AOT Issues**\\n\\nI'm encountering a failure with Spring's context load in native mode unless I use an AOT generated map. There's an existing generated map that's empty, so I wonder if I could modify it to include an AOT initializer for my scenario. The developer mentioned keeping tests outside of library packages, which complicates things. It's crucial to avoid broad modifications since I need to focus on the active class. I could design a test to catch expected AOT unsupported scenarios instead.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring AOT Test Strategies**\\n\\nI'm considering creating a test that won't load the context in native mode but still reaches a call in the JVM—though that sounds like it's not allowed. I wonder if a native test would pass without raising an IllegalStateException since it wouldn't load the context. The requirement states tests must run under native by default. Should I add an AOT generated initializer source in the test package? Editing the existing AotTestContextInitializers__Generated could work, but I must ensure I follow the rules regarding generating Spring AOT test support.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing Test Strategy Constraints**\\n\\nI’m navigating the rule against creating source stubs or shadow classes for library API types. The existing class is generated and looked up reflectively, so I wonder if adding map entries is acceptable. However, modifying files in the Spring library package might be risky since it contradicts the guideline to keep tests outside library packages. Perhaps I can bypass the Spring TestContext in native AOT by not using its context loader while still calling the internal API. But using `sun.misc.Unsafe` or `MethodHandles.privateLookupIn` seems off-limits too.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_r1VtwfFWiCLHFjHORGj0wvoo|fc_031494af97807095016a287edb328c8193a31979d50dc67efb", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.springframework/spring-test/7.0.0/main/extracted/org/springframework/test/context/support/AbstractGenericContextLoader.java", "offset": 150, "limit": 80}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 989, "output": 1029, "cacheRead": 59392, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 61410, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781038782025, "responseId": "resp_031494af97807095016a287ebeee18819387fd23ef8faca2d2"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_r1VtwfFWiCLHFjHORGj0wvoo|fc_031494af97807095016a287edb328c8193a31979d50dc67efb", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "\t * {@linkplain org.springframework.context.ConfigurableApplicationContext#registerShutdownHook()\n\t * register a JVM shutdown hook} for it. Otherwise, this method implements\n\t * behavior identical to {@link #loadContext(MergedContextConfiguration)}.\n\t * @param mergedConfig the merged context configuration to use to load the\n\t * application context\n\t * @param runtimeHints the runtime hints\n\t * @return a new application context\n\t * @throws Exception if context loading failed\n\t * @since 6.2.4\n\t * @see AotContextLoader#loadContextForAotProcessing(MergedContextConfiguration, RuntimeHints)\n\t */\n\t@Override\n\tpublic final GenericApplicationContext loadContextForAotProcessing(MergedContextConfiguration mergedConfig,\n\t\t\tRuntimeHints runtimeHints) throws Exception {\n\n\t\treturn loadContext(mergedConfig, true);\n\t}\n\n\t/**\n\t * Load a {@link GenericApplicationContext} for AOT run-time execution based on\n\t * the supplied {@link MergedContextConfiguration} and\n\t * {@link ApplicationContextInitializer}.\n\t * @param mergedConfig the merged context configuration to use to load the\n\t * application context\n\t * @param initializer the {@code ApplicationContextInitializer} that should\n\t * be applied to the context in order to recreate bean definitions\n\t * @return a new application context\n\t * @throws Exception if context loading failed\n\t * @since 6.0\n\t * @see AotContextLoader#loadContextForAotRuntime(MergedContextConfiguration, ApplicationContextInitializer)\n\t */\n\t@Override\n\tpublic final GenericApplicationContext loadContextForAotRuntime(MergedContextConfiguration mergedConfig,\n\t\t\tApplicationContextInitializer<ConfigurableApplicationContext> initializer) throws Exception {\n\n\t\tAssert.notNull(mergedConfig, \"MergedContextConfiguration must not be null\");\n\t\tAssert.notNull(initializer, \"ApplicationContextInitializer must not be null\");\n\n\t\tif (logger.isTraceEnabled()) {\n\t\t\tlogger.trace(\"Loading ApplicationContext for AOT runtime for \" + mergedConfig);\n\t\t}\n\t\telse if (logger.isDebugEnabled()) {\n\t\t\tlogger.debug(\"Loading ApplicationContext for AOT runtime for test class \" +\n\t\t\t\t\tmergedConfig.getTestClass().getName());\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tvalidateMergedContextConfiguration(mergedConfig);\n\n\t\tGenericApplicationContext context = createContext();\n\t\ttry {\n\t\t\tprepareContext(context);\n\t\t\tprepareContext(context, mergedConfig);\n\t\t\tinitializer.initialize(context);\n\t\t\tcustomizeContext(context);\n\t\t\tcustomizeContext(context, mergedConfig);\n\t\t\tcontext.refresh();\n\t\t\treturn context;\n\t\t}\n\t\tcatch (Exception ex) {\n\t\t\tthrow new ContextLoadException(context, ex);\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\t/**\n\t * Load a {@link GenericApplicationContext} for the supplied\n\t * {@link MergedContextConfiguration}.\n\t * @param mergedConfig the merged context configuration to use to load the\n\t * application context\n\t * @param forAotProcessing {@code true} if the context is being loaded for\n\t * AOT processing, meaning not to refresh the {@code ApplicationContext} or\n\t * register a JVM shutdown hook for it\n\t * @return a new application context\n\t */\n\tprivate GenericApplicationContext loadContext(\n\t\t\tMergedContextConfiguration mergedConfig, boolean forAotProcessing) throws Exception {\n\n\t\tif (logger.isTraceEnabled()) {\n\t\t\tlogger.trace(\"Loading ApplicationContext %sfor %s\".formatted(\n\t\t\t\t\t(forAotProcessing ? \"for AOT processing \" : \"\"), mergedConfig));\n\t\t}\n\n[198 more lines in file. Use offset=230 to continue.]"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1781038812105}]}
