mptyConfiguration` class being a package-private static nested class with the @Configuration annotation, which may require CGLIB or reflection for proper handling. Since it's static and package-private, can Spring access it? Also, will the AnnotationConfig context be able to instantiate it?\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_CJ3WwrEmEgiwMwWn54447hgY|fc_031494af97807095016a287fbf21d881938c54e10ec85e59f7", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.springframework/spring-test/7.0.0/src/test/java/org_springframework/spring_test/TestBeanOverrideHandlerTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "    @Configuration(proxyBeanMethods = false)\n    static class EmptyConfiguration {\n    }\n", "newText": "    @Configuration(proxyBeanMethods = false)\n    public static class EmptyConfiguration {\n    }\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 919, "output": 981, "cacheRead": 77824, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 79724, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781039012566, "responseId": "resp_031494af97807095016a287fa533ac819394fac18ae438607a"}}
